  "title": "6723 - Management Reporting Analyst – Investment & Advisory Industry",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role: Data Analyst</strong></p><p><strong>Industry: Financial Service</strong></p><p><strong>Location: Bras Basah</strong></p><p><strong>5 Days | 8am to 5pm/8.30am to 5.30pm/9am to 6pm/930am to 630pm (flexi)</strong></p><p><strong>Salary: $3500 - $4000</strong><br /></p><ol><li><strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong></li><li><strong>Candidate should preferably have 1-2 years of relevant experience. Entry Level is welcome. Training Provided. </strong></li><li><strong>Investment knowledge not required but preferred</strong></li><li><strong>Synthesize complex data insights into compelling and easy-to-understand narratives that enhance decision-making at the executive level</strong></li><li><strong>High proficiency in data analysis tools (e.g., Excel, SQL, Python)</strong></li></ol><p><strong></strong><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><p><u><strong>Data Collection and Integrity</strong></u></p><ul><li>Collect and consolidate AUM and performance data from various platform providers.</li><li>Carry out maintenance of static data, such as AUM and Performance data, and ensure data accuracy, consistency, and integrity across all systems</li><li>Collaborate with the Technology Team, by providing requirements and performing UAT, to design and implement automated data pipelines and centralized data repositories</li></ul><p><u><strong>Data Analytics</strong></u></p><ul><li>Conduct detailed analysis of the company’s portfolio performance</li><li>Perform attribution analysis to identify drivers of portfolio returns</li><li>Carry out risk-related analytics to monitor exposures and portfolio resilience</li><li>Generate management reports on performance trends, AUM analysis, and other key metrics</li></ul><p><u><strong>Reporting and Communication</strong></u></p><ul><li>Compile monthly performance reports to track Company’s portfolios</li><li>Prepare and publish monthly factsheets for company portfolios</li><li>Deliver clear, concise, and actionable insights to Investment Committee</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>📲Interested candidates, please WhatsApp your resume to: +65 9642 0989 (Han) 📧 Or email your resume to: </strong><a href=\"https://employer.mycareersfuture.gov.sg/jobs/6723-senior-hr-executive-education-sector-marine-parade-35k%E2%80%934k-hr-lifecycle-er-supreme-hr-advisory-f4d18bea51dfbe07dff1bccc5ef1e127/view#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">supreme.cc.han@gmail.com</a><strong></strong></p><p><strong>👤Chaw Chiaw Han | R22106723🏢 The Supreme HR Advisory Pte Ltd | EA 14C7279</strong></p>",
